definitions.definition: A smaller, self-contained part of a larger entity. Often refers to a manufactured object that is part of a larger device .
examples: A CPU is a component of a computer.

definitions.definition: A connected subgraph that is not part of any larger connected subgraph.

main_definition: A smaller, self-contained part of a larger entity. Often refers to a manufactured object that is part of a larger device .
secondary_definitions: ( graph theory ) A connected subgraph that is not part of any larger connected subgraph.
